<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-460-329  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 460 329.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Oct 1 1990 v7 n38 p3(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Cahners-Ziff Publishing Associates LP 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Financial problems continue to plague Dilog as company records$483K quarterly loss. (Distributed Logic Corp., 3rd qtr of FY1990)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bowen, Ted Smalley.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Distributed Logic Corp. (earnings).andO;Ticker:    DLOG.andO;Topic:     LossesProfitThird QuarterRevenueDebtDisk Storage.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Financial problems continue to plague Dilog as company record $483K quarterlylossandM;ANAHEIM, Calif.andP;  -- Distributed Logic (Dilog) has reported losses of $483,000for its third fiscal quarter.andM;At the same time, the company pared its operating costs during the thirdquarter by $400.000, according to company officials.andM;Officials cited sparse sales in the late spring and increased competition inthe DEC third-party storage market as the primary causes of its second losingquarter in fiscal 1990.andM;The company reported a loss of $1.7 million for the quarter that ended Jan.andO;31, which was followed by a nominal gain of approximately $3,000 for thequarter that ended April 30.andM;&quot;The softness in orders in the late spring has since corrected itself a bit,&quot;said John Wilson, Dilog's president and chief operating officer.andM;According to industry analysts, however, the loss is a result of continuingrenue problems for the company.andM;&quot;This is [autumn], and they're referring to slack sales in the spring,&quot; saidMark Matheson, analyst with Crutenden and C., a market research company basedin Newport Beach, Calif.andP;  &quot;An Emulex or System Industries merger would haveto happen to keep them from bottoming out.&quot;andM;Financial results for the three-month period that ended July 31 include a netloss of $482,749, or 19 cents per share, bringing the nine-month fiscal tallyto a net loss of nearly $2.2 million, or 86 cents per share, according toofficials.andM;Revenue for the third quarter were $11 million, down 14.3 percent from the$12.8 million in revenues posted in the third quarter of last year, when thecompany logged a profit of $7,229, officials said.andM;Revenues for the nine-month period that ended July 31 were $33.4 million,which represented a 12 percent decrease from the same period last year,officials said.andM;The company has also been hampered by a consistent lack of cash, according toDilog's Wilson.andM;Dilog's interest-bearing debt swelled from $289,918 at the end of fiscal year1989 to $515,238 in the third quarter of fiscal year 1990, according toofficials.andO;</TEXT></DOC>